  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intra-abdominal hypertension can increase the pleural pressure, and then end-expiratory
      transpulmonary pressures will be turn to negative, Pulmonary atelectasis/acute lung
      injury/acute respiratory distress syndrome will appear. In the group of people who suffering
      intra-abdominal hypertension, the investigators use the pressure of esophagus to speculate
      the Intrathoracic pressure, and to setting PEEP in order to decrease the happening of
      ALI/ARDS, which may decrease morbidity in this population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
